s through the accretion disc rim implying a high\ninclination. However, from radio observations it was found that the angle\nbetween the line-of-sight and the jet axis is smaller than 5 degrees implying\nthat the jet ploughs through the accretion disc in this scenario.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 19 May 2006 14:17:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 17 Oct 2006 17:45:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-11-26"}
